aren't equipped to be providing
the kind of

37:34.786 --> 37:36.621 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
mental health treatment that
most people need.

37:36.654 --> 37:38.957 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, how do you
fix that? What
do you do about it?

37:38.990 --> 37:40.859 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SALLY YATES: Well, there are a
variety of
things.

37:40.892 --> 37:43.695 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
With respect to mental health,
one of the
things that we're doing there
is, first of

37:43.728 --> 37:49.334 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
all, trying to train our law
enforcement officers
in how to identify signs of
mental illness.

37:49.367 --> 37:51.703 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: This is before
these individuals
are arrested or get in trouble
in the first

37:51.736 --> 37:53.438 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
place?

37:53.471 --> 37:55.240 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SALLY YATES: Before they're even
arrested,
exactly, and to be able to
divert them to

37:55.273 --> 37:58.877 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
mental health services, instead
of necessarily
going to prison.

37:58.910 --> 38:03.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then, even within our prisons,
we're providing
funding and training and trying,
when we do

38:03.314 --> 38:07.218 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have folks that are actually in
the prisons,
to make sure that we are
providing the kind

38:07.252 --> 38:11.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of mental health treatment that
they need.
But, really, diversion is the
key here, out

38:11.256 --> 38:13.057 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the prison system to begin
with.

38:13.091 --> 38:17.128 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Do you have a
sense of what
proportion, what percentage of
prisoners today

38:17.162 --> 38:23.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have mental health problems or
other emotional,
however you want to describe it,
issues?

38:23.935 --> 38:27.505 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SALLY YATES: You know, there are
varying estimates
out there, and I think it's
really hard to

38:27.539 --> 38:33.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
